headlines.description: Jordan Canzeri's long touchdown runs on two consecutive drives spurred No. 4 Iowa to a win at Nebraska that sent the Hawkeyes to their first unbeaten season in 93 years.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 4 Iowa wraps perfect regular season at Nebraska

events.name: Baylor Bears at TCU Horned Frogs

headlines.description: Trevone Boykin threw for two touchdowns and ran for another to lead TCU to a 28-21 win in double overtime, ending Baylor's Big 12 title hopes.

video.headline: TCU wins 2 OT battle with Baylor

headlines.shortLinkText: Boykin, TCU ruin Baylor's Big 12 hopes in 2 OT

headlines.description: Greg Ward Jr. threw for 308 yards and three touchdowns to lead Houston to a 52-31 win over Navy on Friday and earn the Cougars a spot in the first American Athletic Conference championship game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ward leads Houston to win over Navy

events.name: Oregon State Beavers at Oregon Ducks

headlines.description: Vernon Adams threw for 366 yards and three touchdowns and No. 18 Oregon extended its winning streak to six games and closed out the regular season with a 52-42 victory Friday over the rival Orego

video.headline: Oregon wins high-scoring affair against Oregon State

headlines.shortLinkText: No. 18 Oregon holds off rallying Oregon State 52-42

events.name: Washington State Cougars at Washington Huskies

headlines.description: Myles Gaskin rushed for 138 yards and two touchdowns, Sidney Jones, Darren Gardenhire and Azeem Victor all returned turnovers for touchdowns in the second half and Washington became bowl eligible
headlines.shortLinkText: Washington knocks off No. 20 Washington State 45-10

events.name: Western Michigan Broncos at Toledo Rockets

headlines.description: Corey Davis caught two touchdown passes as Western Michigan upset Toledo 35-30 on Friday to send Northern Illinois to the Mid-American Conference championship game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Western Michigan upsets Toledo to give NIU division

headlines.description: Brad Kaaya threw for 261 yards and a touchdown and ran for another as Miami continued its surge under interim coach Larry Scott with a 29-24 win over Pittsburgh on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Miami strikes early, holds off Pittsburgh 29-24

events.name: Marshall Thundering Herd at Western Kentucky Hilltoppers

headlines.description: Brandon Doughty threw for 370 yards, including five touchdowns, as Western Kentucky routed Marshall 49-28 to win the East Division of Conference USA on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Western Kentucky overwhelms Marshall in 49-28 win

events.name: Kent State Golden Flashes at Akron Zips

headlines.description: Thomas Woodson threw a touchdown pass and ran for 84 yards to lead Akron to a 20-0 victory over Kent State on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Woodson, Hundley lead Akron over Kent State 20-0

events.name: Eastern Michigan Eagles at Central Michigan Chippewas
Troy Trojans at Georgia State Panthers

headlines.description: Nick Arbuckle padded his record-setting season with 368 yards and two touchdown passes as Georgia State won its third straight game, beating Troy 31-21 on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Georgia State gets third straight win, beats Troy 31-21

headlines.description: Alex Collins ran for 130 yards and three touchdowns as Arkansas secured its first winning record in the SEC since 2011 with a 28-3 win over Missouri on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Collins' 3 TDs leads Arkansas past Missouri

events.name: Boise State Broncos at San Jose State Spartans

headlines.description: Freshman Marquis Young rushed for 240 yards and three first-half touchdowns and UMass held on to defeat Buffalo 31-26 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: UMass turns back Buffalo 31-26 behind Young's 240 yards

events.name: Tulsa Golden Hurricane at Tulane Green Wave

headlines.description: Zack Langelar, Craig Suits and Kolton Schindelar ignited a late rally to lead Tulsa past Tulane 45-34 Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tulsa beats Tulane 45-34 with stunning 4th-quarter rally
